post_text:
Jazz Band 1 and Advanced Band were just informed that they received Division 1 (Superior) Ratings at IGSMA (Virtual) District Contest! Jazz Band 1 even received a perfect score from one judge. Both bands therefore qualified for State Competition, had it been held this year. Fantastic work, Panthers!!

While the in-person contest was originally scheduled for mid-March, it transitioned into an online format where recordings of the bands performing could be sent in for adjudication instead. The results took some time due to the ever-changing nature of world events, but the results are finally in, and we could not be more proud of the band students! Their hard work on challenging music certainly paid off.
text:
Jazz Band 1 and Advanced Band were just informed that they received Division 1 (Superior) Ratings at IGSMA (Virtual) District Contest! Jazz Band 1 even received a perfect score from one judge. Both bands therefore qualified for State Competition, had it been held this year. Fantastic work, Panthers!!

While the in-person contest was originally scheduled for mid-March, it transitioned into an online format where recordings of the bands performing could be sent in for adjudication instead. The results took some time due to the ever-changing nature of world events, but the results are finally in, and we could not be more proud of the band students! Their hard work on challenging music certainly paid off.

post_text:
Hello Prairie Grove Families:
On Wednesday, April 8th, between 2:30 pm and 3:00 pm, the Prairie Grove Bus Drivers want to give their students a shout out to say “We miss all of you” by driving through the neighborhoods. Our buses will drive slowly up and down as many streets as possible waving and tooting their horns.
In keeping with the social distancing guidelines, we ask that everyone stay at home and wave to the buses from their windows, doors, or driveways. Please do not go to the bus stop. Also, we cannot stop to talk.
Please know that the Prairie Grove Bus Drivers truly miss seeing all their students’ smiling faces and we hope that everyone stays safe and well.
text:
Hello Prairie Grove Families:
On Wednesday, April 8th, between 2:30 pm and 3:00 pm, the Prairie Grove Bus Drivers want to give their students a shout out to say “We miss all of you” by driving through the neighborhoods. Our buses will drive slowly up and down as many streets as possible waving and tooting their horns.
In keeping with the social distancing guidelines, we ask that everyone stay at home and wave to the buses from their windows, doors, or driveways. Please do not go to the bus stop. Also, we cannot stop to talk.
Please know that the Prairie Grove Bus Drivers truly miss seeing all their students’ smiling faces and we hope that everyone stays safe and well.

PE Update:
Please make sure your child has gym shoes for PE. Boots do not provide the necessary foot support needed, which can lead to preventable injuries.
Active Panthers! If you have a photo of your child being active outside of school that you would like posted on our elementary PE bulletin board, please have your child bring a copy to Mr. Knutt. Photos can include students participating in sports, working out, playing an “organized” game with friends, etc. Let’s see our Panthers being active outside of school!
